Subject: Expose js_std_promise_rejection_check so embedders driving their own
event loop with js_std_loop_once can still sweep for unhandled rejections.

js_std_loop calls js_std_promise_rejection_check after each microtask drain
so unhandled promise rejections surface on stderr and exit 1. js_std_loop_once
deliberately omits the sweep — it returns to the embedder between drains.

The Node compatibility layer (examples/libs/quickjs/node-main.c) drives its
own loop on top of js_std_loop_once because it also has socket / TLS / fd-
watch dispatch to run each iteration. Without an external way to call the
rejection sweep, a top-level `await main()` that rejects sits forever on
the tracker's list and the process exits cleanly with no diagnostic.

Drop the `static` keyword on js_std_promise_rejection_check and add its
prototype to quickjs-libc.h alongside the existing tracker callback.
---
diff --git a/quickjs-libc.c b/quickjs-libc.c
--- a/quickjs-libc.c
+++ b/quickjs-libc.c
@@ -4721,7 +4721,7 @@ void js_std_promise_rejection_tracker(JS
    asynchrously in case a rejected promise is handled later. Currently
    we do it once the application is about to sleep. It could be done
    more often if needed. */
-static void js_std_promise_rejection_check(JSContext *ctx)
+void js_std_promise_rejection_check(JSContext *ctx)
 {
     JSRuntime *rt = JS_GetRuntime(ctx);
     JSThreadState *ts = js_get_thread_state(rt);
diff --git a/quickjs-libc.h b/quickjs-libc.h
--- a/quickjs-libc.h
+++ b/quickjs-libc.h
@@ -64,6 +64,7 @@ JS_LIBC_EXTERN void js_std_promise_rejec
                                                      JSValueConst reason,
                                                      bool is_handled,
                                                      void *opaque);
+JS_LIBC_EXTERN void js_std_promise_rejection_check(JSContext *ctx);
 // Defaults to JS_NewRuntime, no-op if compiled without worker support.
 // Call before creating the first worker thread.
 JS_LIBC_EXTERN void js_std_set_worker_new_runtime_func(JSRuntime *(*func)(void));
